7:
Ow, ow, ow...
That came out of nowhere... 
What even happened?
15:
I should be fine. Thanks, Rem.
Are Mili and Ram okay too?
20: Yes, we are. Thank you, Subaru.
23:
But... Where is this place?
Hey, Puck, do you know where we
are?
27:
Puck? Are you there?
He's not responding... 
What could this mean?
31:
Perhaps this area is at fault. The
strange phenomenon from earlier
could be the cause.
35:
(That feeling... There's no way... 
Was I transported to another world
AGAIN? What is even going on with
my life?!)
38:
W-well, anyway, we might as well go
take a look around. There's no point
in just standing around here.
42:
We don't need you to tell us that,
Barusu.
Rem, let's go. Miss Emilia, please stay
behind me.
48:
What the... The path went and
changed again! This place is one
hell of a maze...
52:
It seems we've gotten lost in quite
the strange place... And it's all your
fault, Barusu.
57: Say what?! I didn't even DO anything!
71:
Are those... people?
Alk, this way!
76:
Wh-whoa. Looks like they didn't even
need our help, huh?
81:
Indeed. And what's more, it seems
that those were the very monsters
Lilie asked to us to defeat. A simple
double-booking, perhaps?
88:
Oh, look, it's other people! You guys
are actually real, right? This isn't a
dream?
93:
Huh? Y-yes, we're definitely real. May
I ask who you guys are?
98:
Er, well, the thing is... we're a bit lost
here. Think you could escort us to
the exit?
105:
Incredible... To think that such a
splendid city would exist on top of
that maze...
110:
But I've never heard of this place.
"Palpebra," you said?
114:
Subaru and his group already
cleared out the monsters we were
assigned to defeat. We figure it's
only fair the money goes to them.
119:
That's our Alk for you, honest as
always! In that case, I'll go ahead
and give them the reward!
123:
A-a reward? We had merely lost our
waywe did nothing to earn a
reward...
128:
There's no need to be so humble.
This is due compensation for your
deeds back there. Please accept it.
133:
I'm sorry for inconveniencing you
like this... If you insist, however, we
will graciously accept this reward.
136:
I've never seen coins like these... Are
any of you familiar with this
currency?
141:
Say, do you guys know a place
called the Kingdom of Lugunica?
That's where we're all from...
146:
I don't think I've ever heard of a
place called that...
150:
The four of us got sucked into this
strange rift thing, and we suddenly
found ourselves in that maze back
there.
156:
I see... So you're drifters. I should
have expected as much, given that
we found you in the Kaleidoscope.
160:
Drifters? Kaleidoscope? What
exactly do you mean?
165:
I mean to say that people from
different worlds often end up in the
Kaleidoscopethe maze which you
were wandering. You're no longer in
your original world.
171:
This is all very difficult to believe...
However, you don't appear to be
lying either.
175: What will happen to us now, Sister?
181:
Do not be afraid, Rem. No matter
what happens, I will be here to
protect you.
186:
Okay, I think we've got an idea
what's happening now. How about
we continue this conversation
tomorrow?
190:
To tell you the truth, I'm totally wiped
from walking around in that maze
for so long!
195:
Right, of course. In that case, you
should rest up for the remainder of
the day!
199:
Thank you. We're still new to this
place, and there is much we don't
know...
201:
I'm sure Subaru will feel better once
he's gotten some rest.
206:
It's only natural to be overwhelmed
at a time like this.
There's an inn nearby run by the
Guildperhaps you could stay there
for the night?
210:
Hmm, you probably don't know the
process for checking in, right? We'll
go with you and teach you!
215:
Seriously? Thank you, Alk! You're so
reliableyou're like the big boss
around here, huh?
218: B-boss? I don't know about that...
224:
*yawn*
Well then, I suppose we should retire
for the night. If anything comes up,
call me immediately, Subaru.
227:
Gotcha. Thanks.
Have a good night.
231:
Ahh... I have absolutely no idea
what's going on, but at least I didn't
suddenly die or anything.
234:
(There's no guarantee that my
Return by Death will work in this
world... Here's to hoping no other
crazy stuff happens...)
241:
Greetings, traveler from beyond.
Resting without a care in the world, I
see.
260:
(No way, what is even happening?
Am I... going to die like this?
Somebody help me!)
